title: Quickstart
---

# Quickstart

## Writing Content

Create `.rdx` files in the `docs/` directory. RDX is Markdown with embedded components.

<Callout kind="warning" title="Heads up">
Components are embedded directly in your Markdown content. View the source of this page for examples.
</Callout>

## Components

### Callout

Highlighted blocks for notes, warnings, tips, and errors. Use `title` for the header and `kind` for the style: `info`, `warning`, `error`, `tip`.

<Callout kind="info" title="Info">
This is an informational callout.
</Callout>

<Callout kind="tip" title="Tip">
This is a helpful tip.
</Callout>

<Callout kind="error" title="Error">
This highlights an error or danger.
</Callout>

### Tabs

Switchable content panels. Each `Tab` needs a `title`. Selection persists via localStorage when a `group` is set.

<Tabs>
<Tab title="npm">
npm install oxidoc
</Tab>
<Tab title="yarn">
yarn add oxidoc
</Tab>
<Tab title="pnpm">
pnpm add oxidoc
</Tab>
</Tabs>

### CodeBlock

Syntax-highlighted code with optional `filename` header, `language` tag, and line `highlight`.

<CodeBlock language="rust" filename="main.rs" highlight="2">
fn main() {
    println!("Hello, Oxidoc!");
}
</CodeBlock>

### Accordion

Collapsible sections. Use `title` for the trigger text. Multiple accordions are independent by default.

<Accordion title="Click to expand">
Hidden content goes here. You can put any content inside an accordion.
</Accordion>

<Accordion title="Another section">
More hidden content.
</Accordion>

### CardGrid

Responsive grid of cards. Each `Card` supports `title`, `icon`, `href` (makes it a link), and body content.

<CardGrid>
<Card title="Getting Started" icon="🚀" href="/docs/quickstart">
Learn the basics of Oxidoc.
</Card>
<Card title="Components" icon="🧩">
Explore all available components.
</Card>
<Card title="Configuration" icon="⚙️">
Customize your documentation site.
</Card>
</CardGrid>

### Steps

Numbered step-by-step instructions with a connecting line. Each `Step` takes a `title`.

<Steps>
<Step title="Install Oxidoc">
Run `cargo install oxidoc-cli` or use your package manager.
</Step>
<Step title="Initialize a project">
Run `oxidoc init my-docs` to scaffold a new documentation site.
</Step>
<Step title="Start writing">
Create `.rdx` files in the `docs/` directory and run `oxidoc dev`.
</Step>
</Steps>

### Badge

Inline status pill. Use `variant` to set the color: `info`, `tip`, `warning`, `danger`, `new`, `deprecated`.

This feature is <Badge variant="new">New</Badge> in v2.0.

The old API is <Badge variant="deprecated">Deprecated</Badge>.

Status: <Badge variant="tip">Stable</Badge> <Badge variant="warning">Beta</Badge> <Badge variant="danger">Experimental</Badge>

### Tooltip

Hover/focus popup for definitions or abbreviations. Set the tooltip content with the `text` prop.

Oxidoc uses <Tooltip text="WebAssembly — a binary instruction format for stack-based virtual machines">Wasm</Tooltip> for interactive components.

### Tag

Uppercase inline label for categorization. Use `variant` to set the color: `info`, `tip`, `warning`, `danger`, `new`, `experimental`, `deprecated`.

<Tag variant="new">new</Tag> <Tag variant="experimental">experimental</Tag> <Tag variant="deprecated">deprecated</Tag>

### ThemedImage

Swaps images based on the user's color scheme. Use `light` and `dark` for the two sources. Supports `width`, `height`, and `alt`.

<ThemedImage light="/assets/logo.svg" dark="/assets/logo.svg" alt="Logo" width="120" />

### Banner

Dismissible announcement bar. The `persist` prop controls what happens after dismissing:

- `none` (default) — reappears on every page load
- `session` — stays dismissed for the browser session
- `forever` — stays dismissed permanently

Set `dismissible` to `false` to remove the close button entirely.

<Banner id="welcome-banner">
Welcome to the Oxidoc documentation! Star us on GitHub.
</Banner>

### Mermaid

Diagrams rendered automatically from fenced code blocks with `mermaid` as the language.

```mermaid
graph LR
    A[Write .rdx] --> B[oxidoc build]
    B --> C[Static HTML]
    B --> D[Wasm Islands]
    C --> E[Deploy]
    D --> E
```

## Development Server

Run `oxidoc dev` to start a local server with hot reload. Edit any `.rdx` file and the browser refreshes automatically.

## Building for Production

Run `oxidoc build` and your site is generated in `dist/` — deploy it anywhere.
